                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d376">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wetter</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Strobel</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tamatave</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-01-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 27, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 7.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>I regret to say that the report here is prevalent that Mr. Waller absconded.”
                    This I will state: I find he has appointed himself administrator of Crockett’s
                    estate and taken over the entire assets of said estate and carried them with
                    him. As soon as I can I will report in a separate dispatch on this subject.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
